of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":31,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Hulton was born in 1424, in Farnworth, Lancashire, England, his father, James de Hulton, was 36 and his mother, Elizabeth Molyneux, was 28. He married Catherine Knowles about 1447, in Farnworth, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 10 September 1460, in Bolton, Lancashire, England, at the age of 36."},"et":{"1424–10 September 1460":"1424–10. september 1460","1419–Male":"1419–Surnud","1421–Male":"1421–Surnud","1424–1460":"1424–1460","1427–Female":"1427–Surnud","1448–1537":"1448–1537","1459–Female":"1459–Surnud","1388–Male":"1388–Surnud","1397–1442":"1397–1442","10 September 1460":"10. september 1460","1460":"1460","Abt 1459":"umbes 1459","1459":"1459","1448":"1448","1414":"1414","1424":"1424","about 1448":"umbes 1448","1455":"1455","1388":"1388","1421":"1421","1442":"1442","15 August 1442":"15. august 1442","about 1447":"umbes 1447","1397":"1397","1419":"1419","1537":"1537","1427":"1427","Farnworth, Lancashire, England":"Farnworth, Lancashire, England","Bolton, Lancashire, England":"Bolton, Lancashire, England","Farneworth, Lancashire, England":"Farnworth, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1424–10 September 1460":"1424–10. syyskuuta 1460","1419–Male":"1419–Kuollut","1421–Mal